cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category as it deals with the enhancement of reliability in 5G New Radio through multi-connectivity. It may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it presents an analytical study of the outage probability enhancement. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with the cost of resource usage. It may also fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it discusses the selective use of multi-connectivity for critical users. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) as it deals with the transmission of data packets.
